Hah. COSTA Rmn, Volcan de Irazu (Roqers).

One specimen. This species is a close ally of the Colombian H. fulvum, Boh. (the type of which is before me); but differs from it in its more convex shape, the elytra more shining and more coarsely punctured‚ with the margins more broadly expanded at the apa, the prothorax less expanded at the sides and narrowing almost from the base. The antennae are similarly formed in the two specieS, but they are very differently coloured, II. fulvum having the joints 1, 2, and 11 rufo-testaceous and 3-10 black.

Both species differ from the typical members of the genus in having the prothorax very much narrower than the elytra; they have much the facies of certain Hispidae.
